                <h5 class="card-title"><a href="">during the procedure</a></h5>
                <p class="card-text">You will lie or sit in a comfortable chair that has an adjustable back and footrest
                  with your arm extended on the armrest. If you prefer to use a specific arm or vein, make it clear to
                  the person drawing the blood sample. A blood pressure cuff or tourniquet will be wrapped around your
                  upper arm so that the veins fill with more blood. This also makes it easier to see the veins and get
                  the needle into them. It also helps to fill the blood bag more quickly. Next, the skin on the inside
                  of your elbow will be cleaned.</p>
                <div class="read-more"><a href="/users/readMore"><i class="bi bi-arrow-right"></i> Read More</a></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6 d-flex" data-aos="fade-left">
            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-img">
                <img src="/public/assets/img/services details/pic-4.png" alt="...">
              </div>
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title"><a href="">After the operation</a></h5>
                <p class="card-text">After donating blood, you will be seated in an observation unit where you can relax
                  and have a snack. After 15 minutes have passed, you can leave.<br> After donating blood:<br>

                  Make sure to drink plenty of fluids.<br>
                  Avoid strenuous physical activity or heavy lifting for about five hours.<br>
                  If you feel dizzy, lie down with your feet up until the feeling goes away.</p>
                <div class="read-more"><a href="/users/readMore"><i class="bi bi-arrow-right"></i> Read More</a></div>
              </div>
            </div>
